  "prompt": "How many known viruses can infect humans?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, it is estimated that there are over 200 known viruses that can infect humans. This includes well-known viruses such as influenza, HIV, hepatitis, and coronaviruses, as well as many others that cause a variety of illnesses, from the common cold to more serious diseases. It is important to note that the exact number can fluctuate as new viruses are discovered and our understanding of existing viruses evolves. Additionally, with advances in genomic technologies and surveillance, more viruses may be identified as capable of infecting humans in the future.",
